Press Release<br /><!-- NewsDate.start -->December 7, 2006<!-- NewsDate.end --><p style="text-align: center">
<span class="PRTitle"><!-- NewsTitle.start -->Recto: Joining Con-ass is going to a cannibal's 
<br />dinner where senators are the main course<!-- NewsTitle.end --></span></p>
<!-- NewsBody.start --><p>Sen. Ralph Recto today said he will not be attending  the House unicameral constituent assembly because aside from being illegal it would be like attending the necrological services for  the Senate.</p>
<p>From the debates in the Batasan yesterday, one can sense that the House sessions  in the coming days will be a  Senate-bashing party ," he said.</p>
<p>So why would you go  to a party  the likes of you are not welcome ?  If you go, its like honoring an invitation from a group of cannibals to a dinner in which you will be the main course ," Recto said.</p>
<p>I cannot imagine myself sitting through what is essentially a   rump session of the House and listening speaker after speaker malign the Senate. Only a person who likes to be tortured would enjoy that," he said.</p>
<p>Recto, however, clarified that he , like most senators," is for Charter change provided it is done for the right reasons, in the right manner and at the  right time.</p>
<p>In three counts, this con-ass  fails. It is for a self-serving reason. It was through a process that violated the very Constitution itself , and  it is the wrong thing to do at this time when we have more pressing problems to attend to," Recto said</p>
<p>Recto admitted that he was not closing the door on  the idea of our country eventually shifting to a unicameral form of government  but  this must be proposed by a  body which will not benefit from such as shift.</p>
<p>In Charter change, the means is more  important than the end. One cannot profess love for the Constitution while at the same time wantonly violate it ," he said.</p>

